Coal is the major energy resource in China, covering 67 percent of the country's consumption structure of all primary energy resources. Official statistics said that from January to September this year, 4,228 people were killed in 2,337 coal mine accidents. Up to Oct. 10, there were 43 major accidents nationwide. The small township coal mine, with an annual production capacity of 60,000 tons, has all valid documents for production. The accident happened at Taiping Coal Mine of Qingxu County, when 25 persons were working underground. 